pectations.%20However%2C%20no%20family%20tradition%20happens%20automatically%2C%20and%20each%20new%20generation%20must%20determine%20which%20parts%20of%20the%20legacy%20to%20leave%20and%20which%20to%20keep.%20In%20your%20case%2C%20this%20decision%20belongs%20to%20your%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20agree%20with%20your%20wife%20that%20asking%20directly%20is%20your%20only%20option%20for%20an%20advance%20inheritance%20payment.%20After%20all%2C%20your%20sister%20has%20already%20tried%20the%20heavy%20hinting%20method%2C%20and%20while%20you%20refer%20to%20it%20as%20%26quot%3Bgenerational%20wealth%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bfamily%20inheritance%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20money%20is%20your%20parents'.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20there%20are%20ways%20to%20ask%20that%20might%20ease%20your%20discomfort%20and%20increase%20your%20odds%20of%20getting%20a%20%26quot%3Byes.%26quot%3B%20I%20wouldn't%20shy%20away%20from%20reminding%20your%20dad%20that%20his%20parents%20did%20the%20same%20for%20him.%20I%20wouldn't%20make%20this%20reminder%20heavy-handed%20or%20accusatory.%20Instead%2C%20it%20should%20be%20a%20gentle%20way%20to%20introduce%20your%20request.%20Start%20by%20saying%20something%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BHey%2C%20Dad.%20Remember%20how%20Grandma%20and%20Grandpa%20gave%20you%20some%20money%20when%20their%20parents%20died%3F%20I%20was%20thinking%20%E2%80%A6%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%2C%20you'll%20want%20to%20have%20a%20well-thought-out%20financial%20plan.%20Research%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%5C%22%3Einvestment%3C%2Fa%3E%20options%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fbest-high-yield-savings-accounts-rates-right-now%5C%22%3Esavings%20accounts%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20trusts%2C%20and%20determine%20how%20to%20maximize%20the%20financial%20gift%20you're%20requesting.%20Then%2C%20pitch%20this%20plan%20to%20your%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20your%20parents%20are