ing.%20This%20is%20both%20good%20news%20and%20bad%20news%20for%20average%20consumers%20and%20investors.%20After%20all%2C%20lower%20rates%20help%20consumers%20save%20when%20they%20borrow%20money%2C%20but%20they%20also%20translate%20to%20lower%20rates%20on%20savings%20accounts%20and%20money%20market%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20consumers%20who%20want%20to%20%26quot%3Bget%20ahead%26quot%3B%20in%20a%20financial%20sense%20should%20look%20for%20opportunities%20that%20lower%20interest%20rates%20create%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20if%20the%20interest%20they%20earn%20on%20savings%20products%20is%20about%20to%20drop.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20Refinance%20your%20mortgage%20and%20other%20debts%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELower%20interest%20rates%20create%20an%20environment%20where%20refinancing%20some%20of%20your%20loans%20makes%20financial%20sense.%20This%20is%20true%20for%20home%20loans%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fpersonal-loans%2Fbest-personal-loans%5C%22%3Epersonal%20loans%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20even%20auto%20loans%20that%20were%20taken%20out%20when%20rates%20were%20higher%20than%20they%20will%20be%20once%20a%20rate%20cut%20takes%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMortgage%20rates%20started%20dropping%20in%20anticipation%20of%20expected%20rate%20cuts%20from%20the%20Fed%2C%20and%20Jennifer%20Beeston%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rate.com%2Floan-officers%2Fjennifer-beeston-247743%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGuaranteed%20Rate%20Mortgage%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20says%20it's%20a%20great%20time%20to%20check%20in%20with%20a%20mortgage%20lender%20to%20see%20if%20you%20are%20in%20a%20position%20to%20get%20a%20lower%20rate%20and%20save%20money.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20relatively%20small%20rate%20cuts%20can%20lead%20to%20significant%20savings%20when%20you%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fwhen-to-refinance-mortgage%5C%22%3Erefinance%20a%