-8f46-5fa025462937%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EWater%20temperature%20is%20too%20hot%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20lot%20of%20people%20think%20hot%20water%20should%20be%20the%20default%20go-to%20temperature.%20While%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fways-youre-ruining-your-clothes-2019-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehot%20water%20is%20going%20to%20give%20you%20the%20best%20clean%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20using%20it%20often%20isn't%20necessary%20or%20good%20for%20your%20laundry.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUsing%20cold%20water%20is%20going%20to%20allow%20your%20clothes%20to%20last%20a%20lot%20longer%20and%20look%20better%20because%20it%20isn't%20as%20aggressive%20as%20using%20hot%20water.%20It'll%20prevent%20colors%20from%20fading%20and%20holes%20from%20forming.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20thing%20about%20cold%20water%20is%20that%20it%20isn't%20actually%20cold.%20It's%20about%2030%20Celsius%2C%20or%2081%20Fahrenheit.%20You're%20still%20going%20to%20get%20a%20really%20good%20clean%20with%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20like%20to%20think%20of%20hot%20water%20washes%20as%20calling%20in%20the%20power%20washer%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20for%20when%20something%20is%20really%20stained%2C%20dirty%2C%20or%20smelly.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20towels%20and%20sheets%2C%20it%20may%20be%20worth%20throwing%20everything%20in%20a%20hot%20wash%20once%20a%20month%20for%20a%20deep%20clean%2C%20but%20cold%20washes%20can%20and%20should%20be%20used%20in%20between.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20there%20are%20ways%20to%20get%20an%20extra%20good%20clean%20without%20always%20using%20hot%20water.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEvery%20other%20month%2C%20I%20might%20throw%20in%20the%20drum%20on%20the%20machine%20some%20powdered%20laundry%20boosters%20that%20make%20the%20water%20detergent%20work%20better.%20Things%20like%20water%20softeners%20or%20a%20type%20of%20sodium%20carbonate.%20There%20are%20also%20rinse%20products%20that%20have%20a%20low%20pH%20solution%20that%20gets%20dispenses%20during%20the%20rinse%20cycle%20and%20dissolve%20any%20leftover%20residue%20for%20a%20deeper%20clean.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPlus%2C%20you%20reduce%20your%20energy%20usage%20by%2090%25%20when%20you%20stop%20using%20hot%20water%20to%20clean%20clothes.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d0343147-f730-4769-adc9-b6dd6cecdbc9%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EUsing%20too%20much%20product%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThinking%20you%20want%20to%20get%20a%20load%20of%20clothes%20extra%20clean%2C%20you%20might%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fhow-much-laundry-detergent-to-use%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eput%20in%20extra%20detergent%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20But%20this%20isn't%20going%20to%20necessarily%20work.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20too%20much%20detergent%20is%20used%2C%20it's%20hard%20to%20rinse%20out%2C%20leaving%20the%20residue%20of%20it%20on%20your%20clothes.%20Leftover%20product%20on%20clothing%20is%20the%20one%20of%20the%20reasons%20people%20get%20skin%20irritation%20from%20their%20laundry.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20can%20also%20lead%20to%20your%20machine%20working%20harder%20because%20the%20sensors%20can%20tell%20the%20clothes%20aren't%20rinsed%20of%20suds.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20you%20see%20a%20ton%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Flaundry-room-ideas%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esuds%20in%20your%20machine%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20that's%20the%20detergent%20telling%20you%20there%20is%20no%20room%20in%20the%20water%20for%20it%20to%20go%20so%20now%20it%20has%20to%20go%20into%20the%20air.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20I'm%20doing%20a%20small%20refresh%20load%20for%20just%20me%2C%20I%20might%20use%20one%20tablespoon%20of%20detergent.%20For%20a%20medium%20load%20that%20isn't%20too%20dirty%2C%20I'd%20use%20two%20tablespoons.%20For%20a%20really%20large%2C%20pretty%20dirty%20load%2C%20I'm%20use%20four%20tablespoons.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228a406289-324b-4a63-a1e4-06a9b49bcda4%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EUsing%20chlorine%20bleach%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYou'll%20never%20find%20chlorine%20bleach%20in%20any%20dry-cleaning%20operation.%20It's%20extremely%20dangerous%20for%20laundry.%20It%20goes%20deep%20down%20and%20strips%20all%20color%20away%20from%20the%20fabric%2C%20creating%20holes%20and%20uncorrectable%20discoloration.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20an%20alternative%2C%20use%20non-chlorinated%20bleach.%20Maybe%20twice%20a%20year%20after%20washing%20and%20before%20drying%2C%20take%20things%20like%20sheets%20or%20shirts%20with%20sweat%20stains%20and%20put%20them%20in%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fhow-to-wash-clothes-by-hand%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ebath%20with%20hot%20water%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20powdered%20bleach%20to%20soak%20overnight.%20That%20will%20get%20rid%20of%20all%20those%20stains%2C%20but%20without%20stripping%20the%20color.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOr%20you%20could%20spray%20hydrogen%20peroxide%20on%20the%20stain%20and%20wait%20for%20it%20to%20work%20overnight.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBoth%20methods%20blow%20people's%20minds%20because%20they%20really%20do%20work%20at%20restoring%20color%20and%20removing%20stains.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2252fec83d-36c0-4ae9-aa30-e90d557b87b3%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EPutting%20clothes%20on%20a%20timed%20dry%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20would%20never%20use%20a%20timed%20dry%20because%20it%20is%20a%20good%20way%20to%20overcook%20your%20clothes.%20When%20you%20over%20dry%20clothes%2C%20it%20will%20cause%20wrinkles%20hard%20to%20come%20out.%20It's%20also%20one%20of%20the%20most%20hectic%20and%20aggressive%20environments%20your%20clothes%20will%20be%20in.%20You%20want%20to%20minimize%20heat%20whenever%20possible.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20are%20some%20clothes%20I%20wouldn't%20ever%20stick%20in%20a%20dryer%20like%20wool%20and%20silk.%20Those%20should%20be%20dried%20flat%20on%20a%20towel.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESynthetics%20don't%20need%20to%20go%20in%20the%20dryer%20either%20because%20they%20dry%20so%20quickly.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20cottons%2C%20it's%20best%20to%20pull%20them%20out%20of%20the%20dryer%20when%20they%20are%20just%20the%20tiniest%20bit%20damp%20because%20you'll%20prevent%20wrinkling.%20Finish%20them%20off%20air%20drying.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2208d096bd-622f-40d2-8b49-50c17dda2904%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ENot%20pre-treating%20enough%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPre-treating%20clothes%20goes%20such%20a%20long%20way.%20I%20keep%20a%20stain%20remover%20by%20my%20clothes%20hamper%20and%20will%20spray%20it%20on%20stains%20when%20I%20take%20it%20off.%20It's%20best%20to%20treat%20a%20stain%20as%20soon%20as%20possible%2C%20but%20once%20treated%2C%20it%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20washed%20right%20away.%20Often%2C%20leaving%20the%20treatment%20on%20the%20stain%20is%20even%20better%20at%20stain%20removal.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20are%20four%20different%20types%20of%20stains%3A%20grease%20or%20oil%2C%20oxidizable%2C%20enzymatic%2C%20and%20particulate.%20Once%20you%20know%20the%20type%20of%20stain%2C%20it's%20easy%20to%20treat.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOnce%20washed%2C%20make%20sure%20they%20stain%20is%20gone%20before%20drying%20because%20once%20a%20garment%20is%20dry%2C%20it's%20harder%20to%20get%20the%20stain%20out.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3