C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fnike-faces-record-streak-of-losses-as-china-concerns-linger-1032574432%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENike%3C%2Fa%3E%20jumped%20in%20to%20gobble%20up%20market%20share.%20Sure%2C%20there%20were%20some%20boycotts%20and%20busts%2C%20but%20the%20trend%20line%20for%20returns%20was%20up%20and%20to%20the%20right.%20And%20as%20long%20as%20the%20Chinese%20consumer's%20glorious%20rise%20was%20as%20inevitable%20as%20the%20Chinese%20Communist%20Party%20claimed%2C%20gains%20would%20multiply.%20That%20was%20the%20story.%20It%20was%20gospel.%20But%20now%20it's%20falling%20apart.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20once-flowering%20Chinese%20consumer%20is%20languishing.%20US%20companies%20are%20losing%20market%20share%20to%20China-based%20rivals.%20Beset%20by%20political%20and%20economic%20forces%2C%20American%20brands%20can%20no%20longer%20count%20on%20China%20for%20growth.%20That%20changes%20the%20risk%20calculus.%20Why%20invest%20heavily%20in%20a%20market%20that's%20boxing%20you%20out%3F%20Without%20the%20promise%20of%20profits%2C%20American%20firms%20are%20also%20becoming%20less%20willing%20to%20go%20to%20bat%20for%20China%20%E2%80%94%20to%20reinforce%20the%20idea%20that%20China's%20market%20is%20crucial%20to%20the%20success%20of%20their%20futures.%20Beijing%20is%20finding%20itself%20increasingly%20friendless%20in%20Washington%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20weight%20of%20the%20US-China%20relationship%20is%20shifting%20from%20constructing%20mutually%20beneficial%20economic%20ties%20to%20balancing%20antagonistic%20national%20security%20interests.%20Rather%20than%20try%20to%20resurrect%20the%20Chinese%20consumer%20and%2C%20by%20extension%2C%20reestablish%20critical%20economic%20ties%20with%20America%2C%20though%2C%20its%20leader%2C%20Xi%20Jinping%2C%20doesn't%20seem%20to%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BXi%20doesn't%20wake%20up%20every%20day%2C%20look%20at%20the%20economy%2C%20and%20panic%2C%26quot%3B%20Lee%20Miller%2C%20the%20f