't%20share%20the%20same%20values.%20The%20US%20strives%20to%20be%20an%20open%20society%3B%20China%20is%20increasingly%20closed.%20We%20may%20butt%20heads%20in%20the%20South%20China%20Sea%2C%20over%20Taiwan%2C%20over%20resources%20across%20the%20globe%2C%20but%20it%20was%20money%20that%20kept%20us%20together.%20Without%20access%20to%20the%20Chinese%20consumer%2C%20US%20stakeholders%20have%20less%20reason%20to%20see%20China%20as%20a%20market%20and%20more%20reason%20to%20see%20it%20as%20a%20menace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20demand%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20pandemic%20lockdowns%20ended%20in%202023%2C%20the%20Chinese%20economy%20experienced%20what%20is%20known%20on%20Wall%20Street%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bdead%20cat%20bounce.%26quot%3B%20Picture%20a%20dead%20cat%20being%20dropped%3A%20It%20may%20rebound%20off%20the%20ground%20a%20bit%2C%20but%20after%20that%2C%20it's%20going%20nowhere.%20Similarly%2C%20China's%20decimated%20economy%20got%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20pickup%20once%20COVID%20restrictions%20ended%20in%202023%2C%20but%20a%20year%20later%2C%20things%20look%20bleak.%20Beijing's%205%25%20GDP%20growth%20target%20%E2%80%94%20once%20seen%20as%20a%20slam%20dunk%20%E2%80%94%20is%20now%20openly%20in%20doubt.%20Debt%20in%20the%20property%20market%20is%20still%20dragging%20the%20economy%20down%2C%20and%20the%20government's%20bets%20on%20an%20export%20boom%20don't%20seem%20to%20be%20paying%20off.%20Prolonged%20deflation%20erodes%20the%20value%20of%20China's%20currency%20and%20ultimately%20means%20it%20has%20to%20sell%20more%20exports%20to%20make%20the%20same%20amount%20of%20money.%20Unemployment%20for%20Chinese%20young%20people%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2016%20and%2024%20spiked%20to%2017.1%25%20in%20July%2C%20forcing%20a%20new%20class%20of%20(often)%20overeducated%20graduates%20to%20compete%20for%20low-wage%20jobs.%20They're%20being%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Frotten-tail-kids-chinas-rising-youth-unemploymen